<main class="container general-container">
    <div class="row h-100">
        <div class="col-12 my-auto">
            <h4 class="guide-title">Airmed Identity Tutorial</h4>
            <hr>
            <p class="guide-paragraph">This tutorial shows how to create public and private keys to share files securely on the Airmed Foundation platform.</p>
            <section id="create-identity">
                <h6 class="guide-subtitle">Create a new identity</h6>
                <hr>
                <ol>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Press the <strong>Identity</strong> button at the top right corner of the navigation bar. This shows a drop down menu. Select the <strong>New</strong> option.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="new-identity" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/new_identity_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph"> Press the <strong>Generate</strong> button to create a new key pair.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="generate-btn" class="img-thumbnail margin-image" src="images/generate_btn_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">
                            A new identity within the Airmed Foundation network is then created. This identity consists of a <strong>private key</strong> and a <strong>public key</strong>. Both are <strong>cryptographic keys</strong> created using the RSA system. We use the private key to both encrypt and decrypt files associated with an individual. We use the public key to identify this person or entity. We can generate the public key from the private key. A private key is to be kept <strong>SECRET</strong>, as it is what allows a person to access encrypted files on the network.  
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
            <section id="upload">
                <h6 class="guide-title">Upload an encrypted file</h6>
                <hr>
                <ol class="margin-divider">
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Select the <strong>Upload</strong> button at the top left of the navigation bar.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="upload-btn" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/upload_btn_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Select a file with the <strong>Choose a file button</strong> or <strong>dragging the file</strong> to this area.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="choose-file" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/choose_file_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Proceed to check the option <strong>Encrypt file</strong>. Then two inputs will be displayed, the first one mustpress contain the <strong>private key</strong> of the user who is uploading the file. This allows us to validate his identity.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="upload-ie" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/upload_ie_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">After filling the fields, we select the <strong>Upload</strong> button.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="press-upload" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/press_upload_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">After uploading the file, you will be given the <strong>hash of the Blockchain transaction</strong> and the <strong>encrypted IPFS Hash</strong>. The IPFS hash will be needed to recover this file</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="encrypted-ipfs-hash" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/encrypted_ipfs_hash_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
            <section id="download">
                <h6 class="guide-title">Download an encrypted file</h6>
                <hr>
                <ol>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Select the <strong>Download</strong> button at the top left of the navigation bar.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="download-btn" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/download_btn_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">You will have to put the <strong>encrypted hash</strong> generated when <span class="font-italic">* uploading the file</span>. Specify that the file is encrypted and then put your <strong>private key</strong> in the input field. After filling the fields, press the <strong>search</strong> button.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="download-ie" class="img-thumbnail margin-image" src="images/download_ie_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">If the entered data is correct, the file to download will appear listed. Select the <strong>download</strong> button.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="download-finish-step" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/download_finish_step_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
            <section id="identity-files-sec">
                <h6 class="guide-subtitle">List all sent and received files</h6>
                <ol class="margin-divider">
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Select the <strong>Identity</strong> button at the top right of the navigation bar. This shows a drop-down menu. Here select the <strong>Files</strong> option.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="identity-files" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/identity_files_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">After selecting the <strong>Files</strong> option, you will have to write your <strong>public or private key</strong> in the input field and press the <strong>search</strong> button.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="files-search" class="img-thumbnail margin-image" src="images/files_search_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph"> Then two tables are displayed. One has the hashes of the files sent and another has the hashes of the files received.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="tables-search" class="img-thumbnail margin-image" src="images/tables_search_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
            <section id="identity-recover">
                <h6 class="guide-subtitle">Recover public key</h6>
                <hr>
                <p class="guide-paragraph">If, for any reason, you lose your public key you can recover it through your private key.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">Select the <strong>Identity</strong> button at the top right of the navigation bar, this shows a drop down menu. Here select the <strong>Recovery</strong> option.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="identity-recovery" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/identity_recovery_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">You must place your <strong>private key</strong> in input and press the <strong>recover</strong> button.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="recovery-btn" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/recovery_btn_lg.png"/>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="guide-number">
                        <p class="guide-paragraph">After pressing the button, your public key is then displayed.</p>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <img id="recovery-ie" class="img-thumbnail" src="images/recovery_ie_lg.png"/>
                        </div>                        
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>